# mesh_eviction_walk.tas — Walk far enough to evict, then walk back.
#
# Purpose: validate that the per-tick mesh eviction pass keeps the meshed
# chunk count bounded as the player traverses the world, AND that walking
# back into the disc re-meshes the previously evicted chunks.
#
# Default spawn:
#   feet ≈ (24, 64, 20), yaw = -π/2 (forward = -Z)
#
# Plan:
#   t=1..2     Click left to capture mouse (gameplay input gates on this).
#   t=3        keydown W + Shift — start sprinting forward (-Z).
#   t=3203     keyup W + Shift — stop after ~200 sim ticks * sprint 9 u/s
#              * dt 1/120s ≈ 240 blocks ≈ 5 chunks. The player has now
#              crossed five chunk boundaries; chunks at the trailing edge
#              should be > render_distance + 1 away and have been evicted.
#   t=3205     keydown S + Shift — sprint backward (+Z) for the same
#              duration. Re-enters the chunks that were just evicted.
#   t=6405     keyup S + Shift — stop. Player back near spawn.
#   t=6600     Hold steady so the headless shutdown captures a clean state.
#
# Sprint maths (sanity check):
#   dt = 1/120 s   spd = SPRINT_SPEED = 9 u/s
#   movement per tick = 9 / 120 = 0.075 blocks
#   3200 ticks → 240 blocks → 240/48 = 5 chunks
#
# Usage (from utils/swindowzig):
#   zig build native -Dexample=voxel
#   ./zig-out/bin/voxel --headless --world=flatland \
#     --tas examples/voxel/tests/mesh_eviction_walk.tas 2>&1 | grep CHUNK_STATS
#
# Expected log shape — meshed-count should stay bounded by the disc area
# (49 for R=4 + a few hysteresis stragglers, never the unbounded growth
# you'd see without eviction).

# --- Capture mouse ---
1 mouse_down left
2 mouse_up left

# --- Sprint forward (-Z) for ~3200 sim ticks ---
3 keydown W
3 keydown Shift
3203 keyup W

# --- Sprint backward (+Z) for ~3200 sim ticks ---
3205 keydown S
6405 keyup S
6405 keyup Shift

# --- Hold steady so the mesher can catch up on any backlog and the final
#     stats lines land on a stable position. Without this tail the
#     "without eviction" baseline is bottlenecked by MESH_GENS_PER_TICK = 1
#     and undercounts the actual chunk-meshed peak. ---
9000 mouse_move 0 0
